I sorta like it. The graphics are decent for a game like this and it's kind of fun.

My problems

1. In my opinion, it's way to hard to get stars. Where I was it was one star per enemy. And it's pretty hard to kill them. Ether make stars easier to get or make enemy's weaker.

2. The weapons cost to much. This kind of goes with the stars problem. Because it's to hard to get stars, it makes the weapons incredibly expensive. I did 5 runs and only god around 300 stars.

3. To many random things or tiles you can press. A this includes ads and also things that are supposed to be included. At the start I was confused at the start because there we so many random things.

I think this app has lots of things you can improve. But right now I wouldn't suggest it.
Lots of fun,  very addictive accumulating stars for upgrades.

So here is my opinion on this game. This game is really great it's fast paced colorful and just very fun over all so I really recommend playing this game because it even works on iPod touch 12345 gen and can also be a big time spender

It is classic arcade style with the crisp graphics & mechanics of the modern age, fun to play but the potential would come with a larger variety of upgrades, such as increasing the shield amount (more than 100 shield), Increasing toughness (taking less than 10 damage per hit), star unlocks (stars containing power ups or more valuable stars), increase fire rate, unlock additional weapons like high damage rockets that fire from time to time that seek to hit their target, additional fighters, shots capable of neutralizing enemy fire i.e. I shoot a red shot it disappears. perhaps those shots are only fired 1out of ?# shots. With this many available upgrades you decrease costs a little bit. Just some suggestions.

           Thanks,
                     Rocky J. Smith
